{
  "1": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Redefinition and proposal of the new standard Japanese name for Rhinogobius sp. OR morphotype \"Shimahire\" (Perciformes, Gobiidae)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Toshiyuki SUZUKI*, Takahiko MUKAI**, Hidenori YOSHIGOU***, Naoharu OSEKO**** and Darsu TYON*****"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Abstract: Rhinogobius sp. OR morphotype \"Shimahire\" was first reported from a river of Hyogo Prefecture, southwestern part of Honshu, Japan. Subsequent studies revealed that it was genetically and ecologically differed from all other morphotypes of Rhinogobius sp. OR, as well as all other Rhinogobius species in Japan. Nevertheless, comprehensive morphological studies of the morphotype \"Shimahire\" have never been done. We thus compared the morphological details between the morphotype \"Shimahire\" and the other Japanese species of Rhinogobius, based on 300 good-quality images of Rhinogobius sp. BF (including morphotype \"Shimahire\") and some other look-alike species collected from Japan. As a result, the \"Shimahire\" morphotype is clearly distinguished from the others in shape of first dorsal fin, coloration, squamation, and sensory-canal arrangement on head. In this paper, we recognized the morphotype \"Shimahire\" as a distinct and fifteenth Japanese species of Rhinogobius (as Rhinogobius sp. BF), and described its morphology in detail. For suitable protection, the new standard Japanese name, Shimahire-yoshinobori, is also proposed for this species. The scientific name of this species is not able to be identified here, because the taxonomy of Rhinogobius is currently confused worldwide."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Key Words: New Japanese name; Rhinogobius sp. BF; Gobiidae, Japan."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "* 418 2010 2 28 5-40-1 Amagasakikita Senior High School, Tsukaguchimachi, Amagasaki, Hyogo 661-0002, Japan E-mail: trimma-toshiyuki@hop.ocn.ne.jp"
